        "created_at": "2018-05-15T07:58:15Z",
        "updated_at": "2018-05-15T07:58:15Z",
        "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
        "body": "Finally managed to get Android studio gradle to sync (didn't have good internet before)\r\n\r\nStream + error handling when on a port blocking wifi works well now. I'm getting pretty noticeable slowdowns when swiping between tabs, and logcat is reporting a bunch of these types of errors:\r\n\r\n> 05-15 00:52:13.878 13848-13935/com.uclaradio.uclaradio E/OpenGLRenderer: com.uclaradio.uclaradio/com.uclaradio.uclaradio.activities.MainActivity continue jank frame too much\r\n05-15 00:52:15.188 13848-13935/com.uclaradio.uclaradio E/OpenGLRenderer: com.uclaradio.uclaradio/com.uclaradio.uclaradio.activities.MainActivity continue jank frame too much\r\n05-15 00:52:16.068 13848-13935/com.uclaradio.uclaradio E/OpenGLRenderer: com.uclaradio.uclaradio/com.uclaradio.uclaradio.activities.MainActivity continue jank frame too much\r\n05-15 00:52:16.988 13848-13935/com.uclaradio.uclaradio E/OpenGLRenderer: com.uclaradio.uclaradio/com.uclaradio.uclaradio.activities.MainActivity continue jank frame too much\r\n\r\nThis is indicating that the app is performing too much other work on its Main thread, which will cause noticeable UI slowdown. I haven't dug deep into the root cause of the problem, but the profiler may be of help for fixing the slowdown issues. Let me know if these errors are not showing up for you (I ran it on my phone, so the issues should be apparent on other devices as well)"
    },
