        "created_at": "2018-05-15T08:06:44Z",
        "updated_at": "2018-05-15T08:06:44Z",
        "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
        "body": "Also the stream continues to use data even after being paused. The original code (from what I remember) got around this issue by stopping the stream after every pause. A better system may involve stopping after a set timeout when in the app or on a user state event (like exiting the app or screen off).\r\n\r\nFrom exiting the UCLA radio app after playing the stream and then pausing, it looks like it is still using 4G data. If the user of the app is using data for the stream then this could cause high quota usages and bad battery life even when the user thinks the stream was paused"
    },
