        "created_at": "2018-05-15T20:06:27Z",
        "updated_at": "2018-05-15T20:07:12Z",
        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "Sure enough, splitting up those drawables into dpi-specific versions cut down memory usage quite a bit indeed, it's sitting around the 150 MB mark:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/30734384/40080569-35a09d5a-5840-11e8-8de0-a3334869c4b0.png)\r\n\r\nIf your phone has a high pixel density, then this would explain why it was slowing down more for you while remaining pretty smooth for me--my phone falls under the hdpi category, so the OS wasn't scaling the drawables up as much. (Although you did say that there was lag when switching between tabs specifcally. The fluctuation in memory usage when swiping between tabs is just around 5 MB, at least on my device, but while I don't _think_ there's something else going on the background eating memory or causing lag, I could still be wrong).\r\n\r\nLet me know if it's smoother now! (If it's not, could you give me a little more information on your device and the conditions under which it's lagging?)"
    },
